  "voiceover": "He was, by the Guinness Book of Records, the most successful lawyer in history — two hundred and forty-five consecutive murder acquittals, knighted twice, ambassador for two nations at once. Sir Lionel Luckhoo spent his life weighing evidence and persuading juries. Then, at sixty-four, he came to faith in Christ — and did what a trial lawyer does: he put the resurrection on trial. He applied the same standards of proof that had won him 245 straight acquittals — the testimony, the alternatives, the burden of proof. His verdict? 'The evidence for the resurrection of Jesus Christ is so overwhelming that it compels acceptance by proof which leaves absolutely no room for doubt.' The world's most successful lawyer gave his closing argument — and spent the rest of his life making the case for Christ.",
